cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a novel deep convolutional neural network for optical flow and disparity estimation, which falls under the computer vision (CV) domain. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV. The paper also discusses supervised and unsupervised training methods, which suggests the use of machine learning (ML) techniques. Hence, cs.LG (machine learning) is the second likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach to improve the estimation accuracy, which involves replacing deconvolution layers with sub-pixel convolution blocks, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (AI) and neural networks. Therefore, cs.AI is the third likely sub-category. The paper also mentions pose estimation, which falls under robotics (RO), making it the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses experiments and evaluation, which suggests a focus on multimedia (MM), making it the fifth likely sub-category.
